---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Schema from '../../components/Schema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../lib/site';

const ductPrices = [
  { item: 'Whole-home duct cleaning (1,500–3,500 sqft)', min: 399, max: 799 },
  { item: 'Add evaporator coil deep clean', min: 150, max: 250 },
  { item: 'Add dryer vent cleaning', min: 120, max: 180 },
  { item: 'Duct sealing pass (when leaks found)', min: 800, max: 1800 },
];

const faqs = [
  { q: 'How much does air duct cleaning cost in Wesley Chapel & Tampa?', a: 'Most single-family Tampa Bay homes run <strong>$399–$799 in 2026</strong> for whole-home cleaning (1,500–3,500 sqft). Coil deep clean adds $150–$250; dryer vent cleaning adds $120–$180. We quote flat-rate by the home, not by the vent.' },
  { q: 'How often should Tampa homes get duct cleaning?', a: 'Every 3–5 years for most Tampa homes. More often if you have pets, smokers, recent construction/remodeling, or a family member with asthma or allergies. After any water damage, mold event, or rodent intrusion — don\'t wait.' },
  { q: 'Can dirty ducts make me sick?', a: 'Dirty ducts don\'t typically cause illness by themselves, but they can amplify existing conditions — asthma, allergies, sinus issues. More importantly, heavy duct contamination (mold, rodent droppings, biofilm) absolutely affects indoor air quality and should be cleaned.' },
  { q: 'Will duct cleaning lower my energy bill?', a: 'Yes — modestly. A heavy buildup of dust and debris restricts airflow, making your blower work harder and reducing heat transfer at the coil. Most customers see a 5–15% efficiency improvement after a thorough cleaning combined with filter replacement.' },
  { q: 'Do you sanitize the ducts too?', a: 'Our 7-step cleaning includes an EPA-registered antimicrobial fog as the final step — it kills mold spores and bacteria on the duct interior. We only use products rated safe for HVAC use and registered with the EPA.' },
  { q: 'How long does duct cleaning take?', a: 'A typical 3-bedroom Tampa home takes 3–5 hours start to finish. Larger homes or badly contaminated systems can take a full day.' },
];

const related = [
  { href: '/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/', label: 'AC maintenance' },
  { href: '/services/thermostat-installation-tampa/', label: 'Smart thermostat upgrade' },
  { href: '/services/ac-repair-tampa/', label: 'AC repair' },
];

const areaLinks = [
  { href: '/service-areas/wesley-chapel-ac-repair/', label: 'Air duct cleaning in Wesley Chapel', note: 'Epperson · Mirada new-build dust' },
  { href: '/service-areas/new-tampa-heating-and-cooling/', label: 'Air duct cleaning in New Tampa', note: 'Tampa Palms · Heritage Isles' },
  { href: '/service-areas/lutz-home-air-conditioning-service/', label: 'Air duct cleaning in Lutz', note: 'Older homes with attic ductwork' },
];
---
<ServiceLayout
  slug="air-duct-cleaning-tampa"
  title="Air Duct Cleaning in Wesley Chapel & Tampa FL | 7-Step Process | I Care Air Care"
  description="Wesley Chapel NADCA-standard air duct cleaning. 7-step HEPA filtration process, EPA antimicrobial sanitization. Serving Wesley Chapel, New Tampa, Land O' Lakes. Call (813) 395-2324."
  h1="Professional Air Duct Cleaning in Wesley Chapel & Tampa, FL"
  eyebrow="Indoor Air Quality · Wesley Chapel"
  subtitle={`Florida humidity turns HVAC ducts into the dirtiest part of most Wesley Chapel and Tampa Bay homes. Our 7-step HEPA cleaning removes years of dust, allergens, mold spores, and biological contaminants — and leaves a measurable <span class="text-accent-400 font-semibold">indoor air quality</span> improvement.`}
  heroImage="/images/air-duct-cleaning-wesley-chapel-metal-ductwork-supply-vent-register.webp"
  serviceName="Air Duct Cleaning"
  faqs={faqs}
  related={related}
  areaLinks={areaLinks}
  priceRange="$399-$1800"
>
  <h2>Why Wesley Chapel duct systems get dirtier than the national average</h2>
  <p>Every time your AC runs, it pulls air through returns, across a damp evaporator coil, and back through supply runs that have been sweating condensation for years. In Wesley Chapel and Tampa Bay's high-humidity climate, that combination of cellulose dust, pet dander, pollen, and moisture creates <strong>ideal conditions for biofilm</strong> — the slick mold and bacterial layer that coats the inside of HVAC ductwork.</p>

  <p>A NADCA (National Air Duct Cleaners Association) field study found Florida residential duct systems carry <strong>3–5× more biological contamination</strong> than the national average. If you've never had your ducts cleaned, or haven't in 5+ years, odds are strong you're circulating visibly dirty air through every room, every day.</p>

  <h2>Our 7-step air duct cleaning process</h2>
  <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2 text-slate-700 mt-4">
    <li><strong>Pre-inspection with camera.</strong> We send a video camera through key supply and return runs and show you what you're starting with.</li>
    <li><strong>HEPA negative-air containment.</strong> A truck-mounted or portable HEPA vacuum puts the entire duct system under negative pressure, so everything we loosen gets captured — nothing blown back into the home.</li>
    <li><strong>Agitation.</strong> Rotating brushes and compressed-air whips scrub every reachable foot of duct — supply trunks, branches, returns, boots, and the air handler cabinet.</li>
    <li><strong>Register and grille cleaning.</strong> Every supply register and return grille pulled, washed, and re-installed.</li>
    <li><strong>Blower compartment & coil rinse.</strong> The blower wheel, motor housing, and the supply side of the evaporator coil are cleaned — usually the single dirtiest point in a Florida system.</li>
    <li><strong>EPA-registered antimicrobial fog.</strong> Applied to all interior duct surfaces to kill remaining mold spores and bacteria.</li>
    <li><strong>Post-inspection + photo report.</strong> Same camera, same runs. You see the before-and-after.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Signs your Wesley Chapel home needs duct cleaning now</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Visible dust discharge from supply registers within hours of cleaning floors</li>
    <li>Musty or stale odor when the AC first kicks on</li>
    <li>Worsening allergies, asthma, or sinus issues indoors but not outdoors</li>
    <li>Recent renovation, construction, or drywall work</li>
    <li>Evidence of rodent activity (droppings, chewed insulation)</li>
    <li>Water damage event or HVAC flooding</li>
    <li>Pet dander buildup visible in return grilles</li>
    <li>Air handler older than 10 years and never cleaned</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>When duct cleaning is <em>not</em> the answer</h2>
  <p>We'll tell you if duct cleaning isn't the right call — it's not a cure-all. If your main complaint is humidity problems, uneven room temperatures, or constant high bills, the fix is usually a <a href="/services/ac-maintenance-tampa/">proper system tune-up</a>, a duct sealing pass (not cleaning), or in some cases a right-sized <a href="/services/hvac-installation-tampa/">system replacement</a>. We come in, assess, and give you the honest recommendation.</p>

  <h2>What about filter changes?</h2>
  <p>Ducts stay cleaner longer when you run the right filter and change it on schedule. For Tampa homes we generally recommend a MERV 8–11 pleated filter changed every 60–90 days — MERV 13 only if your system is designed for the extra static pressure. High-MERV filters in undersized return systems are one of the most common causes of coil freezing and blower failure we see.</p>

  <p>Ready for measurably cleaner air? <a href="/contact/">Book your cleaning</a> or call <a href="tel:+18133952324">(813) 395-2324</a>.</p>

  <h2>2026 air duct cleaning pricing in Wesley Chapel & Tampa Bay</h2>
  <div class="not-prose my-6 overflow-hidden rounded-xl ring-1 ring-slate-200">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead class="bg-surface text-navy-700">
        <tr><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">Service</th><th class="text-left py-2 px-4 font-semibold">2026 flat-rate</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody class="text-slate-700">
        {ductPrices.map(p => (
          <tr class="border-t border-slate-100"><td class="py-2 px-4">{p.item}</td><td class="py-2 px-4 font-mono">${p.min.toLocaleString()}{p.max !== p.min ? `–$${p.max.toLocaleString()}` : ''}</td></tr>
        ))}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <Schema
    slot="extraSchema"
    type="PriceSpecificationList"
    prices={ductPrices}
    pageId={`${SITE.url}/services/air-duct-cleaning-tampa/`}
    data={{ name: '2026 air duct cleaning pricing in Wesley Chapel & Tampa Bay' }}
  />
</ServiceLayout>
